    <div class="body">
      For all the haters, you can make the hats go away by adding the following rules to the user CSS on your browser: <br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">@-moz-document domain(arstechnica.com) {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; .comment.hat header .author a {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; color: inherit; !important;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; background: inherit; !important;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; }<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; .comment.hat header .author:before {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; background-image: none; !important;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />}</div><br />For Firefox this can be put into your <a href="http://kb.mozillazine.org/UserContent.css" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">userContent.css</a> file, or more easily using the <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/stylish/" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">Stylish</a> plugin. Other browsers should have something similar.
      
